Title: A Relation between the Anomalous Dimensions and OPE Coefficients in

Asymptotic Free Field TheoriesAuthors: Hidenori Sonoda and Wang-Chang Su

Comments: 6 pages, plain TeX, uses harvmac

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B392 (1997) 141-144

In asymptotic free field theories we show that part of the OPE of the traceof the stress-energy tensor and an arbitrary composite field is determined bythe anomalous dimension of the composite field. We take examples from thetwo-dimensional O(N) non-linear sigma model.